WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:55.180
<b>The Summit</b>

21
00:01:59.770 --> 00:02:02.600
Those damn bunnies...
They couldn't have...

22
00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:04.980
Hey, Sanji. What's the matter?

23
00:02:04.980 --> 00:02:06.980
What the heck is going on?

24
00:02:06.980 --> 00:02:09.070
Hey! We gotta run, Luffy!

25
00:02:09.070 --> 00:02:11.530
R-Run? Where?

26
00:02:14.490 --> 00:02:17.280
Doesn't matter where! Someplace far!

27
00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:19.450
What?!

28
00:02:19.450 --> 00:02:22.830
An avalanche...!
An avalanche is coming!

29
00:02:28.590 --> 00:02:32.260
Wapol... Wapol came back!

30
00:02:32.260 --> 00:02:33.260
What?!

31
00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:36.510
Dalton is headed to Bighorn!

32
00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:39.510
Those who can fight,
grab a weapon and head to Bighorn!

33
00:02:39.850 --> 00:02:42.310
Hurry! Those who can fight,
head to Bighorn!

34
00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:44.350
Follow Dalton!

35
00:02:44.850 --> 00:02:46.230
Follow Dalton!

36
00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:47.860
Wapol came back!

37
00:02:47.860 --> 00:02:51.440
Everyone, grab a weapon!
We'll defend our country!

38
00:02:51.440 --> 00:02:53.820
Grab a weapon! Head to Bighorn!

39
00:02:53.820 --> 00:02:56.280
Yeah!

40
00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:03.750
Hey, Vivi. Are you sure we're
headed to Gyasta, where the witch is?

41
00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:07.250
Hmm... When you put it that way,
I'm not really sure...

42
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:09.460
We're in trouble if you aren't sure.

43
00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:14.010
Listen, if Luffy and Sanji make it
to the castle only to find the doctor's out,

44
00:03:14.010 --> 00:03:16.930
they'll think,
"What are we even doing here?"

45
00:03:16.930 --> 00:03:20.720
Unless we locate the doctor soon
and ask her to go back to the castle...

46
00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:22.640
I know that, but...

47
00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:26.140
If you know that, then do something.
You're a princess, right?

48
00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:30.900
That has nothing to do with this.
A princess is not the same as a witch.

49
00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:31.900
But...

50
00:03:31.900 --> 00:03:34.110
Then you look at the map.

51
00:03:34.110 --> 00:03:35.990
What?! Don't be ridiculous!

52
00:03:35.990 --> 00:03:38.570
There's snow everywhere.
The map is...

53
00:03:38.570 --> 00:03:43.040
In any case, there should be
a sign for Gyasta along this route.

54
00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:44.500
So don't miss it.

55
00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:48.830
Got it. Leave it to me!
I'll watch for signs of the sign!

56
00:03:48.830 --> 00:03:50.000
Oh, ignoring me, huh?

57
00:04:01.720 --> 00:04:03.640
Delicious!

58
00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:06.060
Listen up, citizens!

59
00:04:06.060 --> 00:04:10.520
Everything in this country
is my snack!

60
00:04:10.520 --> 00:04:14.110
I'm great! And why is that?

61
00:04:14.110 --> 00:04:16.280
Kuromarimo, tell them!

62
00:04:17.070 --> 00:04:21.200
That's because you're the king,
Your Highness.

63
00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:24.040
That's right! That's exactly right!

64
00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:26.790
A well-done, golden-brown house
is the best, after all!

65
00:04:26.790 --> 00:04:28.330
Yeah!

66
00:04:28.330 --> 00:04:30.750
Your Majesty, I have
some information for you.

67
00:04:30.750 --> 00:04:31.460
What is it?

68
00:04:31.460 --> 00:04:38.420
I received a report that a few Straw Hats
rudely headed toward your Drum Castle.

69
00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:40.680
What? Why?!

70
00:04:41.090 --> 00:04:44.510
It seems they took a sick woman
up to see a doctor.

71
00:04:44.510 --> 00:04:46.100
Well, that's just stupidity!

72
00:04:46.100 --> 00:04:49.810
No one lives in my castle now,
especially not a doctor!

73
00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:56.610
W-Well... I heard that
the outrageous Dr. Kureha,

74
00:04:56.610 --> 00:04:59.240
even more rudely,
lives in Drum Castle now.

75
00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:06.290
What?! That old hag's
living in my castle?!

76
00:05:06.290 --> 00:05:08.450
Just how much does she
intend to mock me?!

77
00:05:08.450 --> 00:05:09.580
Kick her out!

78
00:05:10.330 --> 00:05:13.750
I'll eat her up, along with Straw Hat!

79
00:05:13.750 --> 00:05:16.420
Men, we're going back to the castle!

80
00:05:16.420 --> 00:05:19.010
Yeah!

81
00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:20.010
Stop right there!

82
00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:24.760
Who's that?!

83
00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:29.680
Ahh! He sliced me! I'm gonna die!

84
00:05:30.310 --> 00:05:31.440
Dalton!

85
00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:35.770
I came here to kill you.
You dying suits me just fine.

86
00:05:35.770 --> 00:05:37.530
Dalton, you bastard!

87
00:05:37.530 --> 00:05:40.030
So you're alive!

88
00:05:40.030 --> 00:05:41.490
How dare you harm King Wapol!

89
00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:43.530
Is there a problem?

90
00:05:43.530 --> 00:05:49.500
Do you not control all of the doctors in this
supposed great medical country of Drum?

91
00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:51.000
That's right!

92
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:54.460
Issie 20 Trauma Unit!
Come forward!

93
00:05:54.460 --> 00:05:56.630
Begin the operation.

94
00:05:55.540 --> 00:05:57.500
Begin the operation.

95
00:05:56.630 --> 00:05:58.500
Begin the operation.

96
00:05:57.500 --> 00:05:59.510
Begin the operation.

97
00:05:58.500 --> 00:06:00.590
Begin the operation.

98
00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:01.420
Begin the operation.

99
00:06:00.590 --> 00:06:01.420
Begin the operation.

100
00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:02.220
Scalpel!

101
00:06:02.220 --> 00:06:02.800
Needle!

102
00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:03.760
Tin.

103
00:06:03.760 --> 00:06:04.680
Hammer.

104
00:06:05.180 --> 00:06:07.970
Wow... I really thought I'd die!

105
00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:11.230
Exactly my point!

106
00:06:11.230 --> 00:06:14.230
You alone are protected
while the citizens are forced

107
00:06:14.230 --> 00:06:17.940
to wallow in sickness,
bereft of doctors... Wapol!

108
00:06:17.940 --> 00:06:22.780
Wapol? That's King Wapol to you,
Dalton, my retainer.

109
00:06:22.780 --> 00:06:26.410
Hear, hear! You don't
have the right to blather!

110
00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:30.410
The three of us, you included,
were King Wapol's top brass.

111
00:06:30.410 --> 00:06:32.870
We were his loyal hands, remember?

112
00:06:34.210 --> 00:06:37.040
It is true that when you
were making people suffer,

113
00:06:37.040 --> 00:06:41.340
all I could do was watch,
even though I was right by your side.

114
00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:44.090
I have to take responsibility for that.

115
00:06:44.090 --> 00:06:47.470
Wapol... let us leave
this country together.

116
00:06:47.470 --> 00:06:50.260
We must not stay
in this land any longer.

117
00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:53.520
Dalton! You didn't do anything wrong!

118
00:06:53.520 --> 00:06:54.520
That's right!

119
00:06:54.520 --> 00:07:00.020
You're the only one in the government
who fought for the citizens!

120
00:07:00.020 --> 00:07:01.280
Even at your own risk!

121
00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:06.740
Humph! You should've died
as Drum's captain of the Royal Guard!

122
00:07:06.740 --> 00:07:10.200
I'm surprised that you survived
in this country with no doctors.

123
00:07:10.200 --> 00:07:14.330
Drum is acknowledged internationally
as a country with advanced medicine.

124
00:07:14.330 --> 00:07:17.460
But who would know...
that there were actually

125
00:07:17.460 --> 00:07:22.210
only twenty doctors who worked
in the research facility of the king's castle,

126
00:07:22.210 --> 00:07:26.180
and all the other doctors were exiled?

127
00:07:26.180 --> 00:07:31.640
That's right! Those who become
sick can beg for their lives.

128
00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:36.100
If I feel like it, I might
lend them the Issie 20.

129
00:07:36.100 --> 00:07:41.110
If they don't wanna die, all they
have to do is obey me, the king!

130
00:07:41.110 --> 00:07:46.070
With that, my rule is absolute.
That's the government of this country!

131
00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:48.820
You cannot call that a government!

132
00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:52.160
Humph! You sure speak
your mind, don't you?

133
00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:56.210
Kill him! Kill your ex-captain!

134
00:07:56.210 --> 00:07:59.710
As I figured, you do not
get what I'm saying...

135
00:08:04.090 --> 00:08:08.340
You are the son of the previous king,
who was good to me.

136
00:08:08.340 --> 00:08:11.260
I was hoping that you would
come to your senses some day,

137
00:08:11.260 --> 00:08:12.890
but I was deluding myself!

138
00:08:12.890 --> 00:08:15.390
Ahh! There he goes!
It's the Ox-Ox Fruit!

139
00:08:15.390 --> 00:08:16.640
The bison type!

140
00:08:18.140 --> 00:08:20.690
Don't flinch! Fire!

141
00:08:23.610 --> 00:08:24.560
We can't hit him!

142
00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:25.480
He's dodging them!

143
00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:27.780
I'll show no mercy,
even to my ex-subordinates!

144
00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:32.580
Fiddle Whomp!

145
00:08:41.330 --> 00:08:43.250
Incredible! What power...!

146
00:08:43.920 --> 00:08:47.210
So this is the raw power...
of someone with a zoan-type devil fruit!

147
00:08:47.590 --> 00:08:50.220
I have had it up to here with you all!

148
00:08:50.220 --> 00:08:53.100
A country where the king
is the first to run off

149
00:08:53.100 --> 00:08:55.430
during a time of crisis
should just die out!

150
00:08:55.430 --> 00:08:58.930
You don't stand a chance
against the two of us.

151
00:08:58.930 --> 00:08:59.890
Just give up.

152
00:09:00.900 --> 00:09:03.360
Dalton!

153
00:09:03.820 --> 00:09:04.870
Dalton!

154
00:09:04.870 --> 00:09:06.360
We've come to assist you!

155
00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:07.850
Let us fight with you!

156
00:09:07.850 --> 00:09:10.490
We'll protect the freedom
of this country!

157
00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:14.780
The truth is, I've
known you a long time...

158
00:09:19.580 --> 00:09:21.080
to your ultimate misfortune.

159
00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:22.000
Don't...!

160
00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.380
Your weak point is...

161
00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:40.140
– Why...
– ...did you shield us...?

162
00:09:40.140 --> 00:09:41.060
Dalton!

163
00:09:44.610 --> 00:09:46.020
Dalton!

164
00:09:46.020 --> 00:09:51.360
That's your weak point,
kind-hearted Dalton.

165
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:53.070
This death suits you!

166
00:09:56.700 --> 00:09:58.040
Wh-What's going on?!

167
00:09:58.040 --> 00:10:00.500
Hm? What's going on?
An earthquake?

168
00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:07.250
Hey, this isn't good. We can't
go farther because of the deep snow.

169
00:10:07.250 --> 00:10:09.710
Looks like we went up the mountain...

170
00:10:11.550 --> 00:10:12.590
Huh?

171
00:10:12.590 --> 00:10:15.640
What's... this rumbling?

172
00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:19.390
Usopp! Could this be...?

173
00:10:20.310 --> 00:10:23.350
An... a-avalanche...?

174
00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:26.020
Twenty-five thousand
six hundred thirty-one...

175
00:10:26.020 --> 00:10:27.310
Twenty-five thousand
six hundred thirty-two...

176
00:10:27.310 --> 00:10:30.030
Twenty-five thousand
six hundred thirty-three...!

177
00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:33.530
Hm? What's making all that noise?

178
00:10:42.620 --> 00:10:45.500
Twenty-five thousand
six hundred thirty-four!

179
00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:50.500
Ahhh! Those damn bunnies!
They'll never get away with this! Dammit!

180
00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:53.970
Wh-Wh-Wh-What are we gonna do?!
Wh-Wh-What are we gonna do, Sanji?!

181
00:10:54.630 --> 00:10:55.630
How should I know?!

182
00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:57.010
The first priority is Nami!

183
00:10:57.010 --> 00:10:57.550
The second is Nami!

184
00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:58.390
The third is Nami!

185
00:10:58.390 --> 00:10:59.140
The fourth is Nami!

186
00:10:59.140 --> 00:10:59.930
And the fifth is Nami!

187
00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:01.640
Got that?!

188
00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:03.430
Protect her even if it kills you!

189
00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:05.480
Got it!

190
00:11:05.480 --> 00:11:07.690
But how?!

191
00:11:13.570 --> 00:11:15.780
Ah! Over there! That cliff!

192
00:11:15.780 --> 00:11:16.860
Cliff?!

193
00:11:16.860 --> 00:11:19.740
Run! We need to get
as high up as we can!

194
00:11:21.660 --> 00:11:22.700
It's coming!

195
00:11:32.550 --> 00:11:35.220
Good, we made– Ahh!

196
00:11:35.760 --> 00:11:38.220
Oh no! We're not high enough!

197
00:11:47.190 --> 00:11:48.850
What do I do now?!

198
00:11:49.270 --> 00:11:50.810
Oh, yeah!

199
00:11:52.780 --> 00:11:55.490
Sanji! Grab my hand!

200
00:11:58.200 --> 00:11:59.160
You saved my skin!

201
00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:00.740
Yeah, but...

202
00:12:00.740 --> 00:12:02.700
even though we won't
sink in the snow,

203
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:06.290
we'll go straight down the mountain
if we don't do anything!

204
00:12:06.290 --> 00:12:07.500
What?!

205
00:12:07.500 --> 00:12:09.750
You have got to be kidding me!

206
00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:13.840
We were almost to the base
of that chimney mountain, too!

207
00:12:13.840 --> 00:12:15.970
We were just a step away
from the doctor!

208
00:12:15.970 --> 00:12:18.930
Luffy! Find a way to stop this!

209
00:12:19.640 --> 00:12:22.300
Dammit... Those hopping
bunny bastards!

210
00:12:22.300 --> 00:12:24.720
Next time I see them,
I'll simmer them in a pot!

211
00:12:24.720 --> 00:12:25.390
Ah...!

212
00:12:25.390 --> 00:12:27.350
What?!

213
00:12:38.610 --> 00:12:39.820
What should we do, Sanji?!

214
00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:42.910
There's only one way!

215
00:12:42.910 --> 00:12:45.200
Run!

216
00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:50.170
What the heck's... with them?!

217
00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:57.970
Oh no, Luffy! Look ahead! Ahead!

218
00:12:59.050 --> 00:13:02.050
Ahhh! A rock! We're gonna crash!

219
00:13:06.220 --> 00:13:11.230
You can't crash!
You're carrying Nami!

220
00:13:20.740 --> 00:13:22.740
We're crashing!

221
00:13:24.740 --> 00:13:28.950
You have to treat ladies... gently!

222
00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:31.460
Sanji!

223
00:13:43.930 --> 00:13:45.180
Sanji!

224
00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:47.970
Ahhh... That hit me good...! Dammit!

225
00:13:47.970 --> 00:13:54.650
You idiot! Don't do stuff
like that without telling me!

226
00:13:57.650 --> 00:13:59.860
Ahhh! Sanji!

227
00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:04.530
Sanji!

228
00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:04.530
Sanji!

229
00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:13.670
– Ahh! It's coming!
– It's not stopping!

230
00:14:13.670 --> 00:14:15.330
This village will be swallowed!

231
00:14:15.330 --> 00:14:16.340
Get out of here!

232
00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:23.260
We're getting out of here!
Chess! Kuromarimo! Get on!

233
00:14:23.260 --> 00:14:24.550
Robson!

234
00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:28.430
Robson, Serious Mode!

235
00:14:28.430 --> 00:14:31.930
King Wapol! Please let us ride, too!

236
00:14:31.930 --> 00:14:35.810
Shut up! Get out of here on your own!

237
00:14:36.610 --> 00:14:40.280
Robson! Hurry up!
It's closing in on us!

238
00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:46.990
W-W-W-W-W-W-W-W-W-W-We'll
be fine! Don't worry, Vivi!

239
00:14:46.990 --> 00:14:50.740
Even if we get swallowed,
I'll save you for sure!

240
00:14:50.740 --> 00:14:53.910
Hey, do you think Luffy,
Sanji, and Nami were...?

241
00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:58.880
Could they have been swallowed
by this avalanche?

242
00:14:59.750 --> 00:15:02.920
Ahhhh! Your Majesty!

243
00:15:02.920 --> 00:15:04.510
Ahh!

244
00:15:03.300 --> 00:15:04.510
Ahh!

245
00:15:03.670 --> 00:15:04.510
Ahh!

246
00:15:04.510 --> 00:15:06.720
Ahhhhh!

247
00:16:12.740 --> 00:16:16.160
Nami, are you cold?
Hang in there just a little longer.

248
00:16:17.290 --> 00:16:20.790
Listen. Hold this. Stay here
and wait for me just a little while.

249
00:16:45.730 --> 00:16:47.950
Oh, it was you guys.

250
00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:50.780
No wonder the taste
was like a gross syrup.

251
00:16:50.780 --> 00:16:52.740
They'll never get away with this!

252
00:16:52.740 --> 00:16:53.990
Who do you mean?

253
00:16:53.990 --> 00:16:56.790
Idiot! Them of course!

254
00:16:56.790 --> 00:16:58.460
"Them" meaning...?

255
00:16:58.460 --> 00:17:02.210
You said some of the Straw Hats
are going up the mountain

256
00:17:02.210 --> 00:17:05.170
to the castle right now...
then this happened!

257
00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:09.510
They have a grudge against us
because of what happened,

258
00:17:09.510 --> 00:17:12.470
so they caused an avalanche
on that snow mountain.

259
00:17:14.050 --> 00:17:16.600
Oh no! That's what happened?

260
00:17:16.600 --> 00:17:19.560
Then, this avalanche was their doing...

261
00:17:19.560 --> 00:17:22.020
Let's go! We'll follow them
to the snow mountain!

262
00:17:22.020 --> 00:17:26.650
I'll teach them a lesson
about battling in the snow!

263
00:18:32.010 --> 00:18:34.680
I will definitely get you there.

264
00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:37.050
Don't die...

265
00:18:38.260 --> 00:18:39.600
both of you...

266
00:18:45.060 --> 00:18:46.060
There they are!

267
00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:49.020
Would you look at that,
King Wapol! We've found them!

268
00:18:49.480 --> 00:18:51.490
Hold it, brat!

269
00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:54.240
It's unthinkable
how impertinent you've been!

270
00:18:54.240 --> 00:18:56.200
You'll pay for that!

271
00:19:04.710 --> 00:19:05.750
Move.

272
00:19:05.750 --> 00:19:07.750
Humph! You hippo!

273
00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:09.710
Why should I move?

274
00:19:10.210 --> 00:19:14.630
Looks like what you have on your back
and under your arm are half-dead.

275
00:19:22.310 --> 00:19:23.270
Hold it!

276
00:19:23.270 --> 00:19:25.440
Oh, I know!

277
00:19:25.440 --> 00:19:28.310
Chess! I thought up a new law.

278
00:19:28.310 --> 00:19:29.650
Write this down.

279
00:19:29.060 --> 00:19:29.650
Yes, Sire!

280
00:19:29.650 --> 00:19:33.440
Those who ignore the king
are to be executed!

281
00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:38.660
Ignoring me already?!

282
00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:43.830
Men! Get the sick and injured ones first!
They're ignoring me the most!

283
00:19:43.830 --> 00:19:44.750
– Sire!
– Sire!

284
00:19:44.750 --> 00:19:46.250
What'd you say?!

285
00:19:47.710 --> 00:19:49.380
I'll take the woman on his back!

286
00:19:49.380 --> 00:19:51.090
I'll take the man.

287
00:19:52.670 --> 00:19:53.590
Take this!

288
00:19:53.590 --> 00:19:55.050
Marimo's Surprise!

289
00:19:59.760 --> 00:20:00.760
Listen, Luffy!

290
00:20:00.760 --> 00:20:03.220
Don't you dare fight them.

291
00:20:03.220 --> 00:20:07.140
Whether you attack or get struck,

292
00:20:07.140 --> 00:20:11.310
Nami will feel the whole impact too!

293
00:20:14.570 --> 00:20:16.320
Damn you!

294
00:20:16.320 --> 00:20:19.280
You'll regret this!

295
00:20:19.280 --> 00:20:21.160
Don't follow me!

296
00:20:22.530 --> 00:20:26.040
Humph. What a coward... It's no use!

297
00:20:31.880 --> 00:20:34.170
I'll show him...

298
00:20:34.170 --> 00:20:37.170
what a battle in the snow is like...

299
00:20:44.890 --> 00:20:48.020
Huh...? They're gone...

300
00:20:48.020 --> 00:20:50.980
What's going on? I wonder
if they've already given up...

301
00:20:55.530 --> 00:20:57.530
Now this is a true snow battle!

302
00:20:57.530 --> 00:20:58.780
The white disguise...!

303
00:20:58.780 --> 00:21:00.110
Snow Powder Makeup!

304
00:21:00.110 --> 00:21:03.780
They're so weak,
they'll be dead with just one shot.

305
00:21:05.120 --> 00:21:06.660
Checkmate!

306
00:21:06.660 --> 00:21:10.750
Stop it!

307
00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:18.050
Polar bears...

308
00:21:21.380 --> 00:21:23.350
Lapins?!

309
00:21:25.760 --> 00:21:27.770
Did they protect him?

310
00:21:27.770 --> 00:21:32.650
It's a coincidence. Lapins never
become attached to humans.

311
00:21:44.370 --> 00:21:46.330
Thanks! You saved me!

312
00:21:50.370 --> 00:21:51.750
Don't let him get away!

313
00:21:51.750 --> 00:21:52.620
– Yes, Sire!
– Yes, Sire!

314
00:22:04.300 --> 00:22:07.850
What the hell do they
think they're doing?!

315
00:22:23.490 --> 00:22:25.490
Doctor...

316
00:22:28.990 --> 00:22:30.200
Doctor...

317
00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:35.210
Doctor...

318
00:22:43.170 --> 00:22:45.720
So this is it...

319
00:22:46.140 --> 00:22:48.850
I can't see the top.

320
00:22:53.520 --> 00:22:57.650
I can find the doctor... up there...

321
00:22:59.820 --> 00:23:03.780
Hang in there a little longer,
Nami and Sanji!

322
00:23:53.500 --> 00:23:54.830
Avalanche...

323
00:23:57.330 --> 00:23:59.920
We were swallowed by the avalanche...

324
00:23:59.920 --> 00:24:01.800
Ah! U... Usopp?!

325
00:24:01.800 --> 00:24:03.920
Usopp!

326
00:24:06.510 --> 00:24:10.800
Usopp! Come on! Wake up!

327
00:24:12.310 --> 00:24:14.140
He's still alive!

328
00:24:14.140 --> 00:24:16.640
Usopp! Hang on!

329
00:24:20.900 --> 00:24:22.860
Come on! Usopp!

330
00:24:22.860 --> 00:24:24.400
Usopp!

331
00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:26.780
Oh, Vivi... Don't wake me up.

332
00:24:26.780 --> 00:24:28.990
I was just having a beautiful dream.

333
00:24:28.990 --> 00:24:33.830
A field of beautiful flowers out of
this world and a beautiful river... Oh?

334
00:24:33.830 --> 00:24:35.910
You're almost in the afterlife!

335
00:24:34.450 --> 00:24:35.910
Isn't that Zoro swimming in the river...?

336
00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:37.790
Wake up! Don't sleep! Wake up!
Isn't that Zoro swimming in the river...?

337
00:24:40.670 --> 00:24:45.800
All 74,000 Usopp Pirates, close in!

338
00:24:45.800 --> 00:24:51.890
No! Wake up!
Usopp, don't die! Usopp!

339
00:24:51.890 --> 00:24:56.430
Usopp! Usopp! Usopp!
Usopp! Usopp! Usopp!

340
00:24:56.430 --> 00:24:59.390
Phew, you saved me, Vivi.

341
00:24:59.390 --> 00:25:01.400
Talk about a narrow
escape from death.

342
00:25:01.400 --> 00:25:03.190
I'm glad I'm alive.

343
00:25:03.190 --> 00:25:03.770
But...

344
00:25:03.770 --> 00:25:06.570
don't you think
my face is kinda swollen?

345
00:25:06.570 --> 00:25:08.570
I-It's frostbite! Frostbite!

346
00:25:07.570 --> 00:25:10.780
My head feels kinda heavy...

347
00:25:08.570 --> 00:25:10.780
This is why it's not easy
to be in the snow.

348
00:25:10.780 --> 00:25:12.320
My view looks kinda narrow...

349
00:25:12.320 --> 00:25:13.280
More importantly,

350
00:25:12.320 --> 00:25:14.200
My lips are kinda big...

351
00:25:13.280 --> 00:25:15.830
we need to get our bearings!

352
00:25:14.200 --> 00:25:16.750
Kinda... yeah, I agree...

353
00:25:20.460 --> 00:25:23.710
Ahhh! What's that?!

354
00:25:23.710 --> 00:25:27.460
Ahhh... That was close...
I saw a field of flowers...

355
00:25:30.550 --> 00:25:34.140
Suddenly hitting an avalanche in this cold...
I must've run out of luck.

356
00:25:34.140 --> 00:25:37.100
But this is a sort
of winter swimming, I guess.

357
00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:38.060
Zoro.

358
00:25:38.060 --> 00:25:40.060
Hm? Oh, Vivi.

359
00:25:41.140 --> 00:25:42.020
Huh?

360
00:25:46.610 --> 00:25:50.400
Oh, it's you, Usopp!
What are you guys doing here?

361
00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:52.200
– That's my question!
– That's my question!

362
00:25:55.160 --> 00:25:57.450
What idiots!

363
00:25:57.450 --> 00:26:01.750
That's what you lowly bunnies
get for going against the king!

364
00:26:01.750 --> 00:26:07.750
Humph! I didn't think I'd need to use
my real power on mere bunnies, though.

365
00:26:07.750 --> 00:26:12.090
It couldn't be helped since they're
the most violent animal in Drum.

366
00:26:14.050 --> 00:26:18.390
Just wait... Straw Hat!

367
00:26:26.940 --> 00:26:29.280
Doctor...!

368
00:26:33.700 --> 00:26:36.910
D... Doctor...!

369
00:26:53.300 --> 00:26:55.930
Doctor...!

370
00:26:57.390 --> 00:26:59.430
Ah! Ow!

371
00:27:01.140 --> 00:27:06.100
Sanji!

372
00:27:14.240 --> 00:27:17.780
Th-That... That was close...

373
00:27:20.990 --> 00:27:22.450
Winter swimming?!

374
00:27:22.450 --> 00:27:25.120
Yeah. After swimming
in the river for a while,

375
00:27:25.120 --> 00:27:27.580
I had no idea where I was any more.

376
00:27:27.580 --> 00:27:29.670
So I just wandered while training,

377
00:27:29.670 --> 00:27:31.300
and then I ended up in a forest.

378
00:27:31.300 --> 00:27:34.380
Dressed like that?
You're stupid, aren't you?

379
00:27:34.380 --> 00:27:37.640
Anyway, give me your coat, Usopp.

380
00:27:37.640 --> 00:27:39.100
No way.

381
00:27:39.100 --> 00:27:43.180
Nami might've gotten sick
due to mental exhaustion...

382
00:27:43.180 --> 00:27:45.100
Then your shoes!

383
00:27:44.180 --> 00:27:45.100
No!

384
00:27:45.100 --> 00:27:46.770
One of them!

385
00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:46.770
No!

386
00:27:46.770 --> 00:27:48.150
It's your own fault, isn't it?!

387
00:27:49.150 --> 00:27:51.320
Look over there! There are people.

388
00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:52.110
Hm?

389
00:27:53.690 --> 00:27:57.860
Hey... I remember those buildings...

390
00:27:57.860 --> 00:27:59.120
What?

391
00:27:59.870 --> 00:28:05.830
You're right! This is Bighorn!
So we... circled back!

392
00:28:06.500 --> 00:28:08.830
Step back! Step back!

393
00:28:10.420 --> 00:28:12.420
Dalton is already dead!

394
00:28:12.420 --> 00:28:15.420
There's no way Dalton
would die from an attack like that!

395
00:28:15.420 --> 00:28:18.260
You guys used to serve
under Dalton didn't you?!

396
00:28:18.260 --> 00:28:19.890
Don't you care?!

397
00:28:19.890 --> 00:28:22.760
We're retainers of King Wapol!

398
00:28:22.760 --> 00:28:25.600
If you become an enemy
of King Wapol, you're dead meat!

399
00:28:25.600 --> 00:28:27.350
Hey, what's the matter?

400
00:28:27.350 --> 00:28:29.310
Wh-What's the matter?

401
00:28:30.310 --> 00:28:33.270
What's the matter with you,
dressing like that?!

402
00:28:33.270 --> 00:28:37.150
Dalton's buried under
the snow of the avalanche!

403
00:28:37.150 --> 00:28:38.320
What?!

404
00:28:38.320 --> 00:28:39.990
Dalton is buried?!

405
00:28:39.990 --> 00:28:44.410
Yeah. We can't dig him out
because those guys are in our way.

406
00:28:44.410 --> 00:28:46.830
Step back! Step back!

407
00:28:47.370 --> 00:28:51.790
You can bring your objections
straight to me if you dare!

408
00:28:53.460 --> 00:28:56.590
Usopp, I recognize their clothes.

409
00:28:56.590 --> 00:28:59.930
They're the ones who
attacked us on the sea, right?

410
00:29:00.640 --> 00:29:01.430
Right?!

411
00:29:01.430 --> 00:29:03.100
Yeah, that's right.

412
00:29:03.100 --> 00:29:04.390
They're enemies, aren't they?

413
00:29:03.890 --> 00:29:04.390
Huh?

414
00:29:04.390 --> 00:29:06.520
Enemies! Well, are they or aren't they?!

415
00:29:05.180 --> 00:29:06.060
Huh?

416
00:29:06.520 --> 00:29:09.850
Yea, they're enemies...
but why are you so...?

417
00:29:12.770 --> 00:29:15.780
You aren't so courageous
without Dalton, are you?

418
00:29:21.530 --> 00:29:24.120
What?! Mr. Bushido!

419
00:29:25.370 --> 00:29:26.330
Who's that?!

420
00:29:26.330 --> 00:29:29.910
Hey you! Stop it!
If you attack them, you'll...

421
00:29:32.790 --> 00:29:34.880
This is warm! I'm borrowing it!

422
00:29:35.420 --> 00:29:37.840
You... asked me because of that...?!

423
00:29:38.420 --> 00:29:41.340
Look! They're angry!

424
00:29:40.340 --> 00:29:41.340
You!

425
00:29:41.340 --> 00:29:43.800
You were on the ship
that blew King Wapol away!

426
00:29:44.970 --> 00:29:47.310
Oh? You guys never learn, do you?

427
00:29:48.060 --> 00:29:52.850
Doctor... Doctor...

428
00:29:53.980 --> 00:29:56.730
Doctor...

429
00:30:49.790 --> 00:30:53.960
Hang on...! We're almost there!

430
00:30:53.960 --> 00:30:56.920
Don't you dare die on me!

431
00:32:27.380 --> 00:32:29.760
We made it...

432
00:32:39.480 --> 00:32:40.770
Doctor...

433
00:33:11.260 --> 00:33:14.430
Doctorine... the antibiotics
are responding.

434
00:33:14.430 --> 00:33:18.100
Yeah, I figured that much.

435
00:33:18.100 --> 00:33:21.900
Then, what's the cause? Explain.

436
00:33:21.900 --> 00:33:23.560
It was a kestia.

437
00:33:24.980 --> 00:33:27.110
That's right. A kestia did this.

438
00:33:27.110 --> 00:33:29.570
You go tend to the girl.

439
00:33:29.570 --> 00:33:30.780
Okay.

440
00:34:02.770 --> 00:34:03.350
Who are you?
